40/* machine-dependent definitions: */
41
42/* MAXCHAR is the largest unsigned character value */
43/* MAXTABLE is the maximum table size */
44/* YYINT is the smallest C integer type that can be */
45/* used to address a table of size MAXTABLE */
46/* MAXYYINT is the largest value of a YYINT */
47/* MINYYINT is the most negative value of a YYINT */
48/* BITS_PER_WORD is the number of bits in a C unsigned */
49/* WORDSIZE computes the number of words needed to */
50/* store n bits */
51/* BIT returns the value of the n-th bit starting */
52/* from r (0-indexed) */
53/* SETBIT sets the n-th bit starting from r */
54
55#define MAXCHAR UCHAR_MAX
56#ifndef MAXTABLE
57#define MAXTABLE 32500
58#endif
59#if MAXTABLE <= SHRT_MAX
60#define YYINT short
61#define MAXYYINT SHRT_MAX
62#define MINYYINT SHRT_MIN
63#elif MAXTABLE <= INT_MAX
64#define YYINT int
65#define MAXYYINT INT_MAX
66#define MINYYINT INT_MIN
67#else
68#error "MAXTABLE is too large for this machine architecture!"
69#endif
70
71#define BITS_PER_WORD ((int) sizeof (unsigned) * CHAR_BIT)
72#define WORDSIZE(n) (((n)+(BITS_PER_WORD-1))/BITS_PER_WORD)
73#define BIT(r, n) ((((r)[(n)/BITS_PER_WORD])>>((n)&(BITS_PER_WORD-1)))&1)
74#define SETBIT(r, n) ((r)[(n)/BITS_PER_WORD]|=((unsigned)1<<((n)&(BITS_PER_WORD-1))))

153/* character macros */
154
155#define IS_NAME1(c) (isalpha(UCH(c)) || (c) == '_' || (c) == '$')
156#define IS_NAME2(c) (isalnum(UCH(c)) || (c) == '_' || (c) == '$')
157#define IS_IDENT(c) (isalnum(UCH(c)) || (c) == '_' || (c) == '.' || (c) == '$')
158#define IS_OCTAL(c) ((c) >= '0' && (c) <= '7')
159#define NUMERIC_VALUE(c) ((c) - '0')
160
161/* symbol macros */
162
163#define ISTOKEN(s) ((s) < start_symbol)
164#define ISVAR(s) ((s) >= start_symbol)
165
166/* storage allocation macros */
167
168#define CALLOC(k,n) (calloc((size_t)(k),(size_t)(n)))
169#define FREE(x) (free((char*)(x)))
170#define MALLOC(n) (malloc((size_t)(n)))
171#define TCMALLOC(t,n) ((t*) calloc((size_t)(n), sizeof(t)))
172#define TMALLOC(t,n) ((t*) malloc((size_t)(n) * sizeof(t)))
173#define NEW(t) ((t*)allocate(sizeof(t)))
174#define NEW2(n,t) ((t*)allocate(((size_t)(n)*sizeof(t))))
175#define REALLOC(p,n) (realloc((char*)(p),(size_t)(n)))
176#define TREALLOC(t,p,n) ((t*)realloc((char*)(p), (size_t)(n) * sizeof(t)))
177
178#define DO_FREE(x) if (x) { FREE(x); x = 0; }
179
180#define NO_SPACE(p) if (p == 0) no_space(); assert(p != 0)

195typedef char Assoc_t;
196typedef char Class_t;
197typedef YYINT Index_t;
198typedef YYINT Value_t;

200/* the structure of a symbol table entry */
201
202typedef struct bucket bucket;
203struct bucket
204{
205 struct bucket *link;
206 struct bucket *next;
207 char *name;
208 char *tag;
209#if defined(YYBTYACC)
210 char **argnames;
211 char **argtags;
212 int args;
213 char *destructor;
214#endif
215 Value_t value;
216 Index_t index;
217 Value_t prec;
218 Class_t class;
219 Assoc_t assoc;
220};
221
222/* the structure of the LR(0) state machine */
223
224typedef struct core core;
225struct core
226{
227 struct core *next;
228 struct core *link;
229 Value_t number;
230 Value_t accessing_symbol;
231 Value_t nitems;
232 Value_t items[1];
233};
234
235/* the structure used to record shifts */
236
237typedef struct shifts shifts;
238struct shifts
239{
240 struct shifts *next;
241 Value_t number;
242 Value_t nshifts;
243 Value_t shift[1];
244};
245
246/* the structure used to store reductions */
247
248typedef struct reductions reductions;
249struct reductions
250{
251 struct reductions *next;
252 Value_t number;
253 Value_t nreds;
254 Value_t rules[1];
255};
256
257/* the structure used to represent parser actions */
258
259typedef struct action action;
260struct action
261{
262 struct action *next;
263 Value_t symbol;
264 Value_t number;
265 Value_t prec;
266 char action_code;
267 Assoc_t assoc;
268 char suppressed;
269};
270
271/* the structure used to store parse/lex parameters */
272typedef struct param param;
273struct param
274{
275 struct param *next;
276 char *name; /* parameter name */
277 char *type; /* everything before parameter name */
278 char *type2; /* everything after parameter name */
279};
